 and celebrating success can affirm individual and group identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teaching (Elementary)zJapan. 0aEnglish teachersxPsychology. 0aEnglish teacherszJapanxAttitudes. 0aFilipinoszJapanxAttitudes. 0aFilipinoszJapanxSocial conditions. 0aForeign workerszJapanxAttitudes. 0aIdentity (Philosophical concept)xSocial aspectszJapan. 0aRecognition (Philosophy) 0aRecognition (Philosophy). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aEFL.  aFilipino English Teachers.  acareer narratives.  aidentity politics in language teaching.  aidentity politics.  alanguage teacher associations (LTAs).  alanguage teacher identity.  anon-native teachers of English.  arecognition theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068960008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178892790140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781788927901423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781788927901/original  a978-3-11-068960-0  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-069630-1  PP ROW Ebo